cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.HC 

The paper discusses a machine learning problem related to user feedback and display position bias, which is a common issue in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers a broad range of topics related to statistical learning and data mining. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), which are all relevant to the problem of designing algorithms that can learn from user feedback and optimize display layouts.
